description: Rockaway Beach is a popular coastal area located in Pacifica, California, just 10 minutes south of San Francisco. It's known for its scenic views, sandy shores, and recreational activities such as surfing, beachcombing, fishing, hiking, biking, and more. Right next to Rockaway Beach are restaurants and hotels to spend the day or a weekend away from the hustle and bustle of the city as well as Silicon Valley. This is an opportunity to either develop single-family homes or maximize profit by building condos that can offer mesmerizing ocean and sunset views. Offered here is an approximate 19.5 acres of coastal land, consisting of 10 individual lots all next to each other as one large parcel, each consisting of about an acre. Check with local city planning if SB9 is possible. Buyer to investigate all regulations and permits.
Wonderful  location, build a spectacular home and take advantage of the Ocean Views or a planned unit development

Oversized Ocean view Lot in highly desirable Pedro Point. Included in the price is Architectural plans, soils report, and Survey. This is your opportunity to build your dream home in one of the best areas in Pacifica. Minutes from Ocean, Beach, Hiking Trails, Airport, San Francisco, Bart, and the Peninsula.

Large corner lot with excellent access to the Beaches, Trails, shopping, golf course and schools.  Huge Upside for redevelopment. The lot is fairly flat in the R2 zone, with 4 driveway envelopes at the finished sidewalk. Utilities are adjacent to the property and easily accessible. Great proximity to SFO, the San Mateo peninsula, and downtown San Francisco.  Come enjoy building your coastal lifestyle in Pacifica.

This is 1.96 acres of a parcel of land that is a secluded beach on the Pacific Ocean, in the City if Pacifica. The access to the beach is from an easement next to 528 Esplanade Ave. Cross Street is Manor Dr. West of Highway 1. This secluded beach is adjacent to the cliff that has Esplanade Beach Overlook Trail.   There are Pacifica Esplanade Beach and Mussel Rock Park on the North, and Pacifica Municipal Pier on the South side. It's just a few minutes walking distance from Starbucks, 24-hour Fitness, Walgreens, Safeway, McDonald's, and Chit-Chat Cafe.

The Hinton Ranch! 2 lots left- each over 2 acres!  The feeling being on this property is something you need to experience for yourself.  It's a dream come true to find 2+ acres to build the house you've always imagined.  Truly live in the country on your own acreage and still commute to SF/SFO within 15 minutes.  6 and 8 Hinton Ranch are vacant land, ready for you to build to suit.  The development plan allows one home per lot.  Utilities are nearby according to the site map.

An incredible 5.5 acres lot, atop Pacifica, perched above historic Sharp Park Golf Course, with Ocean Views from Marin Headlands to Pedro Point, surrounded by nature, at the end of newly paved private cul-de-sac and utilities are accessible to site. Incredibly private, devoid of street lights, the revealing night skies are as majestic as the frequent whale sightings & unobstructed sunset Ocean Views. It feels far away yet incredibly close - only 15 min to SFO & San Francisco and 30 min to Palo Alto, minutes from beach, beachfront restaurants, shops, schools, major shopping centers, hiking trails away from traffic. No HOA. Uniquely special - it is outside of coastal commission jurisdiction, not at risk of long-term coastal flooding & benefits from city infrastructure for water, sewer, electric & fiber. Typically properties like these are in the middle of nowhere, on wells, septic & satellite. There is nothing else on or off market like this parcel. It is not in the jurisdiction of coastal commission, not at risk of coastal flooding, and benefits from city infrastructure - water, sewer, electric, and fiber.  The proposed architectural design has 3 levels of grand entertaining, rich amenities, pool & extraordinary spaces connected by balconies & elevator. No HOA. Plans upon request.

A rare opportunity in esteemed Willowbrook Estates, Pacifica!     Own 6.6 acres with a breathtaking Pacific Ocean panorama. Once-in-a-lifetime prospect not to be missed!  Savor the dramatic vista, unmatched in Linda Mar. Sunrise, sunset, crashing waves - nature's spectacle from your dream home.    Five parcels, endless possibilities. Create a sprawling family compound or explore other development opportunities. Craft your bespoke sanctuary to fulfill your desires and complement your lifestyle.    Convenience and tranquility combined. Close to town, with easy access to amenities, shopping, and dining. Just 2.5 miles from the sandy shores of the Pacific, offering the perfect blend of coastal living and urban accessibility.     Pacifica prides itself on forward-thinking development. The city mandates to build nearly 2,000 new homes, and you'll find yourself in the midst of a visionary landscape where growth meets opportunity. As you plan your own private retreat, you can rest assured that the city's innovative approach to expansion will only enhance the appeal of your investment.    This property promises unparalleled views of the glistening ocean, providing a daily dose of natural inspiration. Embrace the tranquility and beauty of coastal living at its finest.

Own an expansive acreage consisting of 30 parcels in beautiful Tobin Park.  Ideally situated at the end of a culdesac in the  Willowbrook Estates neighborhood of Pacifica.  Property is close in town and only 2.5 miles to the beach. Property has  street frontage and runs all the way back with some flat areas and rolling hills.  Enjoy the tranquil surroundings and views of the lush green hills with possible water views at the top of the property.  Possibilities include development for an enclave of private estates, vineyard, horse property, multi-residential, or clearing for growing fields like lavender where demand currently outpaces the supply.  Pacifica's new mandate to build over a thousand new homes makes this a great investment.  The first few photos are renderings to imagine all the possibilities!
Two large lots in the Rockaway section of Pacifica. Lots are currently zoned B-10/HPD with the City and appear to have no improvements.

Building plans are approved by the City of Pacifica!...Ready to start the permit process and begin construction of this beautiful 4 bedroom, 3 bath, 3,128 sq. ft. home...Situated on almost 1 acre lot with beautiful Valley and Ocean views makes this a special property...
This property is surrounded by open space, next to walking, hiking, biking trails...only a short distance to Linda Mar State Beach offering excellent surfing and fishing...close to shopping and transportation... Build your dream home, live in the country, yet less than 30 minutes to SF and SFO Airport, easy access to the Silicon Valley corridor.... Currently available: building plans, topo/survey map, soils report...All utilities available at street (Higgins Way). Also, has potential to build an Accessary Dwelling Unit (ADU).

WOW! 180 degree, UNOBSTRUCTED OCEAN VIEWS! One of the FEW lots on the ENTIRE California coast in a great location, with a blank slate to create your masterpiece with views like this UNDER $1M! Unreal Views! You don't want to miss this opportunity. Previously had verbal approval from the city to build 3 condos. 3 bedroom condos in this area sell for almost $2M! What an opportunity to consider building multiple units to sell, hold for Air B n B/ocean view rental, Or, build one large single family to suit your family's vacation needs or every day use - what a getaway! Imagine the peaceful sound of the ocean lulling you to sleep! Walking distance to the pier, cute coffee shops/restaurant/stores in the downtown area on Palmetto Ave. Lots of remodeling activity in neighborhood houses. Up and coming area! Less than 15 miles to SFO, Pac Bell Stadium in SF, 18 miles to Half Moon Bay, 43 miles to Apple campus. Don't let this once in a lifetime opportunity pass you by!
